I arrived here by googling "How do I report a Jira bug?".   I appear to be at the right place, because I can select "Jira" from the project list.

However, this is not at all clear, because the heading of the page is "Welcome to the Confluence Project".    So am I supposed to submit Jira bugs here or not?

It would be an improvement to clarify this.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an Application Link between JIRA and FeCru
# Create a Project in JIRA named {{DEMO}};
# Create two issues in this project;
# Create a Project in Crucible named {{CR-DEMO}};
# Create a review in this project;
# Commit something with the following message:
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
CR-DEMO-1 is my review and the issue is DEMO-2
{noformat}

h3. Expected Behavior
As per [Viewing an Issue's FishEye Changesets|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Viewing+an+Issue%27s+FishEye+Changesets]:
bq. So the key will need to be at the start of the string, or a character on each side that is not a-z, A-Z, 0-9 or the dash '-' character.

And therefore it's expected that this commit will only appear in the Source Tab of the issue with key {{DEMO-2}}.

h3. Actual Behavior
The commit will appear in the Source tab of both issues ({{DEMO-1}} and {{DEMO-2}}).

h3. Notes
I've checked the JIRA FishEye Plugin source code - in the {{FishEyeUtil.java}} file it's mentioned:
{code:Java| borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
    public static String makeIssueKeyRegex(String issueKey) {
        return new StringBuilder().append("(^|[^a-zA-Z0-9-])")
                .append(issueKey)
                .append("($|[^a-zA-Z0-9-])")
                .toString();
    }
{code}
And if that's the case it should indeed be matching only the issue key then; the regex would be:
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
(^|[^a-zA-Z0-9-])DEMO-1($|[^a-zA-Z0-9-])
{noformat}
which would exclude {{CR\-DEMO-1}}.

